text: Don't miss this adorable cream puff situated in the private gated community of Sea Links in Birch Bay. This home is embraced by a beautifully manicured quiet neighborhood. The back patio features a private setting overlooking the greens. Kitchen is lined with Granite countertops and new sparkling clean appliances. Enjoy walking trails out your back door. Take a stroll in just minutes to Birch Bay Waterfront Beach and restaurants. This home has a brand new water heater, and a brand spanking new roof! The new roof install is completed on May 25th, 2024. A new sump pump and drainage update has also been completed in the crawl space. This is the perfect home if youre looking for a quiet neighborhood close to the beach.

Welcome to this stunning 2020-built home! On the main level you will enjoy the flow from living room to family room with lovely stone surround gas fireplace. The kitchen is a culinary delight with quartz counters, ample cabinets, stainless appliances, and spacious pantry. The slider leads to a sizable deck in the fully fenced back yard. Newer wooden blinds adorn each window for privacy. The garage has additional storage racks and a sealed floor. Upstairs you will find the primary bedroom with new flooring, a walk-in shower and double vanity along with a walk in closet. There is room for everyone with the additional three spacious bedrooms, office space and full upper bathroom.

Live the lake life in the Glenhaven Lakes community! Level building site next to Cain Lake with a brand new 2 bedroom septic installed! Walking distance to community amenities, beach, Reed lake and country store! Water hook up available at the street and lot has been cleared and ready for a beautiful home to be built. Quick stroll to the clubhouse where you will find a heated swimming pool, tennis court with basketball hoops and beach for launching kayaks and fishing. Boat launchs and hiking trails in the neighborhood makes this an adventurous place to live year round or build a income producing property. 20 minute commute to Bellingham or Mount Vernon and 90 minutes up to Mount Baker for skiing and summer hiking!

Welcome to Fairhaven's most charming REMODELED 2-story home you can live in, rent out, or Airbnb! 1109 12th St charms from the curb & delivers throughout. Enter the bright, open living room w/its cozy office or small BR. Then proceed to the masterfully-redesigned kitchen. Stainless appliances, Shaker cabs, quartz counters & vertical tile backsplash. A spacious dining nook looks onto the courtyard-style backyard. Laundry+Full Bath on the main as well. Upstairs is a large Primary BR, guest BR & spacious 3/4 Bath. Walk-out basement for the bikes, toys & tools. Forced Air heat, new Water Heater + Service Panel / Electric. South-side schools, easy bus access & you get to enjoy Fairhaven's dining, shops, parks & galleries literally steps away!

Welcome to a tastefully updated home in a quiet, South Bellingham park. Very bright and open layout. Home has been updated inside and out with new kitchen: cabinetry, high quality stainless steel appliances, lighting and quartz counter tops. Both bathrooms completely remodeled. Laminate flooring throughout main living spaces and bedrooms. Mini split provides A/C. Carport, tons of parking, patio area & storage shed. Close to parks, trails and shopping.

Amazing home surrounded by nature in picturesque Glenhaven! Boasting many finished rooms, 5 bathrooms, 2 rooftop decks, sauna, and high-end finishes, there are two sections to this home: main residence on the north and additional suite on the south. Features include eucalyptus hardwood floors, granite countertops, slate tiles, backsplash in kitchen, and stainless steel appliances. Two rooftop decks great for entertaining, stargazing, and watching fireworks. Close to Lakes Whatcom, Samish, Padden, Cain, and Reed. Fruit trees: apple, cherry, peach, plum, and pear. Successfully used for short-term rental. Plenty of parking: off street, driveway, under portico, and on south side of add'l suite.

Luxury in Semiahmoo UNDER $1M! Welcome your guests into the open concept living/dining/kitchen connected to outdoor living area. Primary bed/bath on the main, 2 bed/1 bath tucked away on the second floor. Room for additional living space/workout area/office upstairs. Quartz countertops, upgraded stainless appliances, cozy gas fireplace. Live an active lifestyle close to trails, water sports & more. Close to Semiahmoo Golf & Country Club, luxurious Semiahmoo Resort, go crabbing in Drayton Harbor, enjoy done-for-you landscape maintenance, & a thriving social communityall for under $1M. HOA dues= Semiahmoo $810/semi-annually + Sea Smoke $246.25/qtr. for a total of $2605 Annually/$217.08 mo.

Thoughtfully remodeled 3 bedroom home in a great park. Welcome to Mt Baker Mobile Home Park located in a beautiful wooded setting off Cedarville Rd. This renovated 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom features double paned windows, open style kitchen with new stove and sink, new flooring throughout, fresh paint inside and out and a new huge carport! Home also has a ductless mini-split for low heating costs and cool A/C on those stuffy summer nights! And the best part about this park?? Lot dues are only $500.00!!!! Come and check out the inexpensive sweet life in the country. So close to Nugent's Corner market, ICU and more! Owner financing possible to qualified buyer. 25% down, 9% interest, 15 year amortization with 5 year balloon.

Welcome to your new home in Mountain View Mobile Estates! This charming 3 bed 2 bath gem in the 55+ community boasts recent upgrades including a nearly brand new roof, exterior & interior paint, and upgraded flooring throughout as of May 2022. Head outside and savor the ample space of your backyard this summer. Benefit from the generous storage provided by two sheds and the convenience of a carport. This home perfectly captures the essence of the ideal living experience, blending comfort, value, and affordability seamlessly. Pets are welcome with approval from the park manager.

Come discover the latest 20 lot phase in Hannah Creek by Skeers Construction. Gorgeous setting backs to a forested greenbelt with creek. This home lives like a rambler with all the bedrooms on the main level. Upstairs is a very large, open bonus room with a 3/4 bathroom. This would be an amazing creative space for crafters or artists, a flexible home office layout, 2nd living area, extended guest bedroom, gym, or home theater. Modern, great room floor plan. Open kitchen has big walk-in pantry. Oversized primary suite. Miles of trails to explore on the adjacent 3000 acre Galbraith Mountain trail system, and Whatcom Falls Park is just down the street. Feels like a world apart, but downtown is less than 3 miles away.

Luxurious Geneva home w/ unobstructed views of the shimmering waters of Lake Whatcom & lovely Canadian Mountains. Light filled, open concept & vaulted ceilings in this spacious 3058 sq ft, 4 bed /3.5 bath, w/office, 3-car garage & RV parking. Gourmet chefs kitchen features: SS appliances, large island w/eating bar & pantry. It opens to a massive great room w/ a gas fireplace. The view decks & hot tub are right off the dining w/stairs to the fenced gardens & fruit trees. The primary bedroom suite has a gas fireplace & a garden tub. The detached studio there for your ideal use. Tranquil, private & sitting high on the hillside taking in gorgeous sunrises & sunsets & just minutes to Galbraith Mountain trails & Lake Whatcom.

Beautifully-updated home, set in peaceful Sudden Valley, with easy access to town, the lake, nature, hiking, biking, and much more! Step inside to an open-concept floorplan boasting hardwood floors, vaulted ceilings, ample natural light, a cozy gas fireplace, and the gourmet kitchen with a pantry, breakfast bar, and recently updated SS appliances. Head upstairs to a full guest bath, and 4 bedrooms including the spacious primary suite with walk-in closet and relaxing 5-piece private bath... Don't miss the stunning modern tile shower! Private low-maintenance backyard on a serene greenbelt, boasting a deck, mature landscaping, and visits from wildlife. Attached garage, and a fabulous location... Don't miss out on this Sudden Valley gem!

Welcome to this quiet cul-de-sac on Hawthorne St. Lovely single level home in well-established neighborhood within blocks of Ferndale High School. This home offers an open main living/dining/kitchen area, 4 beds 1.75 baths & bonus room. Enjoy a kitchen with newer stainless-steel appliances and granite countertops. Enjoy summer evenings on the spacious back deck and brick patio overlooking a large fully fenced back yard. There's even a spot for an outdoor TV. Room for RV Parking. This home is waiting for you to make it your own. Close to I-5, schools, and the main spit of Ferndale's growing downtown community. This location is ideal!
See survey in supplements and pictures. Build your dream home on this 16, 297 sq. ft. homesite. Near Emerald Lake and close to all amenities in Bellingham. Check it out today! Emerald Lake area.

You are going to love this 2 bedroom 1.75 bathroom fully accessible ground level condo. This 55+ community is located in the heart of the Cordata neighborhood making getting to where you are going incredibly easy. This home features newer stainless steel appliances, new LVP flooring throughout, new hot water heater, granite countertops and so much more! The unit also has 2 single car garage spaces that can be used for parking, hobbies and/or additional storage. All this located at secure & pet friendly El Dorado with all its amenities. Very well managed and maintained: greenhouse, dog park, access to walking trails, clubhouse for activities with secure mail & two apartments you can rent for out-of-town visitors.

Rare Opportunity Side by side commercial storage/condo units, in-town location! Each approx. 20' X 60' (1215 sf), and a 3/4 bathroom shared between the two units. Front and rear 13'W X 14'H garage doors for easy ingress/egress. No turning around or backing out necessary! Walk-in door access as well. 30amp and 50amp 220V plug-ins, ample electrical outlets, epoxy sealed floor, Berko industrial heater, and installed interior water spigot. Security gate with access pad, RV sewer dump, community bathroom access, street side mailboxes for personal/business use. Easy access in or out.
Come see this remodeled condo, most everything new!! You won't be disappointed, ready to move in, very clean and bright.

This 5.09 acre lot with gorgeous mountain views is the perfect location to build a custom home. With well-drained sandy loam soils, this is ideal acreage for farming or livestock. Tucked securely in the foothills and out of the path of the Northeastern wind there are many potential building sites on high dry ground, and room for an ADU, shop or barn. New well in place, septic system design for a 6-bedroom septic has been applied for and driveway installed. Highspeed internet available, natural gas in the street, 15 min to Bellingham, near river access & boat launch at Nugent's Corner, private paved access on a dead-end road. The Douglas Fir Christmas Tree Farm adds to the beauty of the landscape.

Exceptional details & breathtaking views! Expansive waterfront panorama highlight mountain vistas. Vaulted ceilings, fireplace, dining w/buffet & wet bar creates effortless entertaining. Chef's kitchen, designer cabinets & Dacor 6 burner, sub zero, eat-in island , radiant heat while overlooking Drayton Harbor. Light beams fill the great room w/cozy 2nd fireplace. Elevator for easy access to lower level. Refined elegance with 3 bed/5 bath. Main primary-fireplace, 2 vanities, radiant heat, tub, shower & walk-in closet. Downstairs boasts 2 guest ensuites, huge wine cellar, 4th fireplace/bonus room, powder room & MORE storage. Semiahmoo optional membership golf, tennis, pool & spa. Marina, Resort, 15 min Canadian border-easy commute Seattle

Welcome home to Festival Square, one of Bellingham's most desirable 55+ condominium communities. This rarely available, easily accessible ground-level 1, 038 sq ft, 2 bed/1.75 bath unit enjoys a peaceful location at the end of a quiet cul-de-sac. Sunny, west-facing windows and deck overlook a serene 15-acre protected nature preserve with a spring-fed pond, home to Bald Eagles, Herons, and songbirds. Affordable HOA dues include Water/Sewer/Garbage/Cable/lawn service and more. Financially healthy Association with well-maintained buildings. Clubhouse on property. Pet's allowed (some restrictions). Great central location in Cordata close to medical, shopping, services, parks, and miles of trails. ADU accessible, no steps.

Welcome to your dream home in Bellingham's coveted Columbia neighborhood. This meticulously remodeled gem offers 2 bedrooms, 1.5 baths, and an inviting open living space, perfect for modern in town living. Step outside to your own private oasis, complete with a thoughtfully landscaped fenced yard, fire ring, gazebo with hot tub, as well as a covered BBQ patio. Garden enthusiasts take note of the front garden beds! One car garage/shop with tons of built in storage, and two private off street parking pads provide room for everything. Walk to parks, shops the waterfront and more! What more could you dream of? This beauty will not last long!

This is that one property you've been looking for. Perfect Property for that dream Home of yours. Geneva building site on 1.4 acres near the top of the hill with great view possibilities. Property is quite secluded away from the road. Mostly treed with saleable timber or selectively take off a few trees to build your dream home and leave the rest for ultimate privacy. Imagine living in your own park and walking, hiking or biking on your own trails. Utilities are at the road, sewer at property line.

Step up to affordable living in the heart of Sudden Valley with this charming, well-maintained single-level home. Featuring an open-concept design and vaulted ceilings throughout, the free-standing propane fireplace adds a cozy, cabin-in-the-woods ambiance. Perched on a hillside, the large wrap-around deck offers a perfect spot to soak in the peaceful setting. The home includes ample storage space below the living room and sits on an oversized lot, presenting numerous expansion opportunities. Enjoy the abundant community amenities and the convenience of being just minutes from Bellingham. Discover the perfect blend of comfort, potential, and natural beauty in this inviting home.

Affordable living in Friendly Ferndale! This home is ready for new owners with a new roof, new furnace and AC, recent Exterior paint, new water heater, new lighting, new stove and dishwasher, all new plumbing and insulation underneath the home, and much more! Inside you'll love the vaulted ceilings and large windows that bring in plenty of natural light. Great open layout with 3 bedrooms and 2 baths. separate laundry room off kitchen. Covered front porch with ramp access. Great yard with space for gardening, fenced area for pets, lots of parking with the 2 car carport and large driveway. Storage area inside carport too. Low space rent of $500 per month and no age restrictions!

Discover spacious living at its best! This wonderful home boasts an expansive lot with ample parking, RV space, and a large backyard perfect for gatherings. Flooded with natural light from the floor-to-ceiling windows, the interior features a grand family room with striking stone fireplace, soaring cathedral ceilings, a dining area, and kitchen with granite countertops. 5 comfortable bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, a versatile loft, and a fully finished basement complete with a woodshop. Everything you need for the ultimate comfortable living experience is right here!

Country living just minutes from Barkley Village, schools and Lake Whatcom. This property has been prepared for your home construction. The view is open to Lake Whatcom, Bellingham Bay and East City areas. Water well has been drilled and is included for your homesite. A 4-bedroom septic design is included. The driveway is in, power is on the property, and you have choices where to build, place your shop and or a barn. This property gives you the best of everything. Easy access, quiet location, close to jobs, shopping and schools. Also, services are either already in place or designed. At this price if you wait it will be too late! Lot size is approximate. Adjoining lot to the West is also listed for sale! Old buildings have little value.

Beautifully updated Fairhaven Square Condo! Light & bright open-concept floor plan w/ soaring ceilings, new LVP flooring, & charming Juliet balcony w/ French doors & west-facing sunset views. Designer kitchen w/ SS appliances, breakfast bar & modern sink w/ built-in cutting board attachment. Dedicated dining area, office nook, & sunny living room w/ balcony access. Light-filled primary suite w/ walk-in closet & large windows, full bathroom w/ updated tile flooring. New light fixtures/ceiling fan & fresh paint throughout! In-unit Washer/Dryer. Shared rooftop deck, gated garage parking w/ designated space, secure building entry, & located in the heart of Fairhaven near Boulevard Park, Interurban Trail & Fairhaven Village Green. Welcome Home!

Nestled beside a tranquil creek, this captivating home offers a harmonious blend of serenity and convenience. With a spacious two-car garage and three inviting bedrooms, it combines practicality with comfort. Discover the joy of nearby shopping amenities while unwinding on your private patio, embraced by the soothing sounds of nature. Your pet will adore the dedicated fenced area, while you gather around the fire pit for enchanting evenings under the stars. Delight in the modern comforts of central AC, sprinklers, and stainless steel appliances, including a new fridge. Lots of sunlight through the ample windows, infusing the main living room with warmth and brightness. Come home to a haven where tranquility meets modern convenience.

Quintessential Northwest Retreat! This well maintained, 2512sf, log/contemporary home is surrounded by a 13, 318 sf ft landscaped double lot that's a woodland gardener's paradise! Nestled in nature on a quiet hill above Lake Louise & on a dead end street only steps away from the Louise Loop walking trail. 3 bdrms+loft, 2.5 baths, AC, heat pump, gas FP, hardwood floors, 2 yr old roof, many updates. 2 car attached garage w/for E-car potential + extra offstreet parking. Sit back in the sun on the deck or in the private garden and listen to the birds. Keep your kayak on the rack just a short walk away at Sudden Valley's AM/PM beaches. Enjoy SValley's amenities: golf course, marina, swimming pool, security & more. This is a rare find for sure.

You will love the curb appeal & everything about this easy living one level home. It features include central air conditioning, manicured yard with sprinkler system, spacious covered patio for outside enjoyment complete with beautiful water features & views of the pond. The interior of the home is in move in condition. It has an open & airy feeling with high ceilings & an open concept living. The spacious living room is open to the informal dining area and kitchen. It also has an formal dining room which could easily be used as an office. The kitchen features lots of cabinets, hard surface counters with nice appliances. The primary suite is spacious with a corner fireplace and great sized walk in closet. You won't want to miss this one.

Welcome to this updated mid-century style home w/ a detached guest house and garage! Situated on a picturesque private acre, minutes to Gailbraith, parks, trails & town. Unique low maintenance, live edge cedar siding. Inside, 2 granite fireplaces - living room & kitchen, cathedral ceilings & stunning line of vertical windows bringing nature in. Newer LVP flooring & carpet. An updated kitchen w/ stainless steel appliances & eco-friendly PaperStone counters. The primary suite w/ large walk-in shower, closets galore & an adjacent office/nursery. French doors lead to a large patio, then on to a charming guest house with full kitchen, washer/dryer, walk-in closet, Victorian style bath & a cottage garden. Guests? Income? Yes, all of it!

Experience casual elegance in this modern designed home with green-belt at the rear & filtered views of Lake Whatcom and the Stewart Mountains from the front. First level has a large 2-car garage; half bathroom; and large laundry room. The 2nd level has a wonderful open design with Living Room, Kitchen (with island) & Dining Room. Rear patio area off of the Dining Room. The Kitchen has white cabinet package with light quartz countertops & stainless steel appliances. Elegant stone 'floor to ceiling' gas fireplace is a wonderful centerpiece in the Living Room. The office and another half bathroom completes the 2nd floor. Upstairs has the Primary Bedroom with onsuite bathroom and walk-in closet. Two other bedrooms & a full bath up.

750 square foot (30x25) industrial/storage condominium conveniently located in the Irongate Industrial Business Park. Quality built with steel construction and metal roof for longevity and low maintenance in mind, and a gated community, STOREHOUSE, that is secure and accessible 24/7. Features include an ADA bathroom, large 14x16 overhead door with windows and automated opener, high vaulted ceiling, wired for 220 and additional outlets, lighting, shelving, epoxy floors, and so much more. Why rent when you can own.

This cozy, stylish Home is 3 bd 2 Bath situated on almost 5 acres and is offering tons of space for hobbies or work with the spacious shops and detached garage! Oversized 3-bay shop is connected to its own electrical meter making it perfect for personal use or to lease out for additional income! Detached 2 car garage with loft and carport perfect for your boat or camper! Endless opportunities in developing this beautiful piece of land with the potential to build your dream home on the back half of the property. Enjoy all the area has to offer with the State Park, boat launch, and grocery stores all close by! Not to mention that Grandview is the driest road in the winter!! 20 min. to Bellingham. And 15 Minutes to Canadian border.

This is the home you have been waiting for! Four bedroom home with soaring ceilings and plenty of space to call your own. The location can't be beat! Across the street from a trail that takes you right down to the beach and shopping in just a few minute walk. Home also sits on a lot that backs a vacant drainage lot so there are no, and never will be, neighbors behind this gorgeous home. Main level features formal living and dining rooms and family room is open to the large kitchen. Huge laundry room leaves lots of room for storage. Upstairs has 4 nice sized bedrooms. Primary suite has huge bathroom with separate shower and tub and large walk in closet. A fully fenced dog run can be found through the dog door in the laundry room.

Charming single-level 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom home nestled in a quaint Ferndale location! Interior features include great room floor plan with convenient built-ins and new LVP floors, offering the perfect space for cozy gatherings. The family room boasts a welcoming pellet stove, adding warmth and ambiance to the space. Primary suite offers a walk-in closet, double sinks, and tub along with a separate shower. Outside, enjoy newer decking and the fully fenced backyard, a gazebo, and hot tub, perfect for outdoor enjoyment. With RV parking available, this home offers convenience and versatility. Located close to schools, a bus stop, and easy access to I-5.

Beautiful like-new home, built in 2019 w/ many upgrades. The open great room concept welcomes you in with vaulted ceilings, cozy gas fireplace & hard surface floors thru the entry, great room, kitchen & dining area. The light, bright & very open kitchen design has self-closing slide out drawers, a full size pantry cabinet, island sink and all upgraded LG appliances stay! (yes, even the Washer/Dryer stay). The main floor Primary bedroom's MASSIVE walk-in closet & storage cubby are HUGE, and the walk-in tile shower is impressive. Upper floor has (2) additional bedrooms, a full bath plus a bonus room! All this in an affordable gated community for privacy & security. Lot backs to an Open Space Tract too!

What an incredible opportunity for home ownership in Bellingham! Perfect for a first-time home buyer or anyone looking for the ideal spot. 2 Beds, & 2 baths with a lovely living area where you can sit by the fireplace & read a good book. There's no age restriction, & this is a stand-alone home featuring a 1 car garage & a perfect backyard to garden or allow pets to play. Cook or host guests in the modern kitchen boasting granite countertops & stainless steel appliances. Additional features: This house backs up to a walking trail. Newer home built by Grandview Homes. Also includes a deck, hardwood floors, custom cabinets and a custom German-made fridge to fit the space perfectly. Close to everything Bellingham has to offer!

Unique Opportunity to enjoy Coastal living in a dream location with partial ocean views and a 5 min walk to the beach! This 2 bedroom, 1 bath home is located on a quiet Cul-de-sac and on a spacious lot backing on to a green space. Vaulted ceilings and large sun filled windows make the interior bright and inviting. Extra Large Patio with plenty of room for outdoor dining, sunny days and relaxing evenings. Separate spacious laundry room with sink and plenty of storage. Brand new roof, gutters, down spouts and skylights installed in March 2024.

Breathtaking mountain views from this gorgeous home in a secluded cul-de-sac. This spacious 5-bedroom sanctuary with tons of natural light boasts an additional bonus room, encompassing 4283 sqft of luxurious living space. Retreat to the primary bedroom oasis featuring a cozy fireplace & indulge in relaxation with the private bath complete with a lavish jetted tub. Entertain with ease in the elegant dining room enhanced by vaulted ceilings & skylights, creating an ambiance of sophistication & warmth. Around the corner you will find the wet bar, including sink, fridge, & storage, a welcome addition to any entertaining space. Unwind in the sauna or gather around the fireplace. This home is the epitome of comfort & luxury-living at its finest!

Custom designed rambler built in 2017 by Pioneer Post Frame with metal siding and roof makes for easy care living on this tree lined 10 acres providing ultimate privacy. The open floor plan with vaulted ceilings and two sets of French doors floods the home with light and walk out to the covered wrap around porch to relax and enjoy your private oasis. Easy care vinyl plank floors and carpet in the bedrooms with radiant floor heat and freestanding wood stove is nice and cozy. The large primary bedroom with an ensuite bath. The level and sunny acreage has a large garden and fruit trees. The storage container shop with covered carport. Not on leased land. The RR5A zoning allows property to be subdivided (buyer to verify). Close to the bay.
nearby_schools: Lummi High School, Lummi Elementary School, Ferndale School District

text: Great opportunity to own a classic, water-view, downtown Blaine home with rare, mixed-use zoning! Located less than 1 mile from the Canadian border with easy access to I-5. Walking distance to the growing and vibrant downtown Blaine scene. Mature landscaping and a wrap-around front porch are perfect for watching beautiful sunsets over the marina as well as the 4th of July parade. This home is zoned for either residential, commercial, or both. It would make a great home-office. It has been used in the past as a primary residence, a residential and commercial rental, a real estate office, law office, and accounting office. Listed as 2 bd. With garage, easily could be 3 or 4 bd. Possibilities are endless.

New construction! Est completion May 30. This brand new 3 bed, 1.75 bath is located in a serene setting, with the back of house facing a beautiful woodland scene and view of Kendall Lake. The vaulted ceilings create a light and airy feel inside. Kitchen and bathrooms are outfitted with quartz countertops. The primary bedroom has an attached en-suite with shower, while the full bathroom with shower and tub is accessible to the rest of the house. The exterior insulation has been upgraded beyond the building code requirements for better home temperature efficiency and noise dampening. Additionally, the interior walls have been insulated for noise dampening between rooms. The house is a blank canvas waiting for you to make it home!

Discover privacy and tranquility in this 5-acre park-like setting. View kaleidoscopic sunsets and partial Bay, Island and Olympic Mountain views. Pacific Northwest craftsmanship includes wood beams, custom woodworking and main- level living. Enjoy energy efficiency with solar panels on the shop, a heat pump, solar water and radiant floor heating. An expansive 3-bay shop with RV parking and 1/2 bath allows for vehicle storage, woodworking and hobbies. Exercise year round in the commercial-grade indoor pool surrounded by glass sliders. Gardeners will covet the fenced garden with fruit trees, grape vines, berries and newly planted vegetable beds. All within minutes to downtown Bellingham, Barkley Village, shopping and amenities.

Welcome home to this nearly new 2 bedroom, 2.5 bathroom home, with 1, 537 sq. ft. with an oversized garage. Floor plan is designed to make the most of the sunny, western exposure. Upon entering the main floor, you will discover a bedroom and an additional bonus room that can serve as an office, TV area, or occasional guest space. The upper level houses the great room and primary bedroom, along with a covered deck that offers views of stunning sunsets. The kitchen boasts quartz countertops, modern cabinets with undermount lighting. Conveniently located near shopping, restaurants, the downtown waterfront and marina, parks, trails, mini golf and easy I5 and border access as well.

This beautiful Cornwall Park home is located just steps from Broadway Park. Well maintained and extensively remodeled, this home retains its period charm. Completely updated bathrooms and kitchen, new paint inside and out, and freshly refinished hardwood floors are just the beginning. The classic custom built-ins and original front door have been restored to their original classic look, showing off the custom tilework surrounding the fireplace. Primary bedroom on the main level has cedar-lined closet. Large bedrooms with walk in closets upstairs. Large walkout basement space for workshop or storage. Fully fenced back yard and detached garage off the quiet alley behind. Close to downtown, waterfront, and all the best Bellingham has to offer.
neighborhoods: Broadway Park Historic District, Cornwall Park

text: Welcome to this inviting home nestled in the sought-after Whatcom Falls neighborhood. Featuring 3 bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, and a spacious bonus room/4th bedroom, this residence offers flexibility to accommodate diverse needs. Relax in the cozy living room, anchored by a gas fireplace and flooded with natural light from the massive windows. Situated on a 10K SF lot, the property boasts a lush backyard with mature trees and shrubs, perfect private dinners on the deck. Positioned towards the rear of the lot, the home provides ample front yard space with plenty of parking, including covered space for an RV. Enjoy the convenience of walking to Lake Whatcom + Whatcom Falls Park, or take a short drive to Galbraith Trails, Whole Foods, or downtown.

Here is what you have been looking for! A well appointed single level home in Barkley Meadows! Walk to Barkley Village, the movie theater, Sunset Square or Lowe's! The vaulted ceilings and well planned layout make this home feel larger than it's square footage. Come in and see the new granite countertops, stainless steel sink, and new kitchen faucet. Also rest assured that you'll always be warm as the furnace was replaced in 2022 and to deal with Bellingham's hottest days know that there is a 2023 installed heat pump that will provide air conditioning. The washer and dryer, which convey, are also brand new! Walking distance to Bellingham's Railroad trail to take you anywhere you want to go by bike or foot.

Welcome to a warm and inviting single-level haven, nestled within the heart of a picturesque small town. With 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms, this newer construction home embraces you with its open-concept living space and custom fireplace, offering moments of relaxation. The kitchen, a masterpiece of design, beckons you to create memorable gatherings and culinary delights, while the covered deck invites you to unwind amidst captivating mountain views. Embrace the serenity of the expansive lot, where nature's beauty surrounds you, creating the perfect backdrop for treasured moments. Located just steps from the Canadian border and a short 40-mile drive to the renowned Mt. Baker ski resort, indulge in the allure of convenience and natural beauty.

Presenting Salmonberry #206! This modern studio boasts high-end finishes like SS appliances, quartz countertops, & designer cabinetry. Luxury vinyl plank flooring combines durability with elegance. Complete with in-unit W/D, 2 storage closets, & ample natural light, all essentials are covered. Accessible via stairs or a ramp for a no-step entry, this 2nd-floor unit offers convenience for all. Nestled in the heart of Lynden, enjoy easy access to amenities. Yet, what truly distinguishes this unit are the serene surroundings. Open the door to reveal breathtaking views of Fishtrap Creek, lush trees & distant mountains. FHA approved, rental cap not exceeded. Ideal for first-time homeowners or savvy investors. Don't miss out on this opportunity!

Welcome to this gorgeous Ferndale home! There is so much to fall in love with at this home, including nearly 2, 700 sqft, 4 bedrooms, 3 full bathrooms, a 3 car garage and dreamy backyard. This home makes it so easy to entertain downstairs with two living spaces, a large kitchen, an open floor plan, backyard complete with newer Trex deck, hot tub and patio space. Downstairs also features a large office space, laundry room and an indoor sauna! Head upstairs where you will find 3 generous sized bedrooms and an oversized primary suite with walk in closet, large bathroom and balcony with partial Mount Baker views. Lovely Ferndale neighborhood with this home located near schools and in a cul-de-sac. This home is ready for you!
